# L2-SYN-026 N-record look-ahead demonstration fixture.
#
# Five records (80 bytes) hand-crafted to demonstrate the value of
# raising the look-ahead depth above the default N=2. The structure
# is "decoy chain" — two valid records, then a corruption block, then
# one more valid record:
#
#   bytes  0-15  : record 1 — valid BC_TO_RT IRIG record
#   bytes 16-31  : record 2 — valid BC_TO_RT IRIG record
#   bytes 32-63  : 32 bytes of all-0xFF — invalid Type Words at every
#                  2-byte position (msg_type=0x7F, not in known set)
#   bytes 64-79  : record 5 — valid BC_TO_RT IRIG record
#
# At N=2 (default): find_first_record accepts offset 0 because the
# 2-record look-ahead chain reaches only record 2, which is valid.
# Iteration decodes record 1, then validate_record at offset 16 fails
# (look-ahead at offset 32 is garbage). Sync recovery scans forward
# through the garbage and finds record 5. Total CSV: header + 2 rows
# (record 1 + record 5).
#
# At N=4: find_first_record at offset 0 walks the look-ahead chain to
# records 2, 3 (garbage), 4 (garbage). The 3rd / 4th look-ahead lands
# on the 0xFF region — invalid Type Word — so the entire chain
# starting at offset 0 is rejected. find_first_record scans forward;
# no 2-byte-aligned offset within records 1-2 produces a valid Type
# Word with an in-range IRIG timestamp; eventually accepts offset 64
# (record 5). Total CSV: header + 1 row (record 5 only).
#
# The N=2 vs N=4 contrast (2 rows vs 1 row) is exactly the L2-SYN-026
# value proposition: deeper look-ahead lets the decoder detect that
# the "valid-looking" prefix is followed by a corruption pattern that
# defeats the default 2-record window, and refuses to commit until it
# finds a record region that survives a deeper sanity check.
#
# Record-1 / record-2 / record-5 byte layout (same template):
#   bytes 0-1 : Type Word 0x0802 (BC_TO_RT, wc=8)
#   bytes 2-3 : ts_upper 0x180F (day=192, hour=15)
#   bytes 4-5 : ts_middle 0xDB20 (min=54, sec=50, us_hi=0)
#   bytes 6-7 : ts_lower 0x0000
#   bytes 8-9 : IRIG Cmd 0x7962 (RT=15, Receive, SA=11, dwc=2)
#   bytes 10-11: Data[0] — varies per record (0x0001 / 0x0002 / 0x0005)
#                to break L2-SYN-018 homogeneity defense and to make
#                the CSV rows distinguishable
#   bytes 12-13: Data[1] 0x0000
#   bytes 14-15: Status 0x0000
0208 0F18 20DB 0000 6279 0100 0000 0000
0208 0F18 20DB 0000 6279 0200 0000 0000
FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF
FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF FFFF
0208 0F18 20DB 0000 6279 0500 0000 0000
